  "preamble": "The alveolar lateral approximant [l] shifts to the voiced retroflex flap [ɽ] through place assimilation in South Asian languages, particularly in retroflex harmony environments. This transformation occurs in Hindi, Tamil, and other Dravidian and Indo-Aryan languages where retroflexed consonants trigger retroflex spreading to adjacent segments.",
